<BlogLayout
  title="Kata Runtime Offloading and Performance Optimization on DPU"
  description="Offloading Kata Container virtualization and emulated devices to a DPU for deployment density and concurrent startup efficiency."
  lang="en"
  category="Project Case Study"
  date="2023 — 2025"
  readingTime={2}
  kind="project"
>
  <h2>Background</h2>
  <p>
    Volcano Engine DPU team is dedicated to offloading virtualization to DPU (Data Processing Unit) to improve deployment density and reduce costs.
    Kata Container is an open-source secure container runtime at ByteDance. This project completed QEMU Kata Container virtualization offloading to DPU.
  </p>

  <h2>Main Work</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Completed QEMU Kata Container virtualization offloading to DPU</li>
    <li>Completed emulated device offloading to DPU</li>
    <li>Optimized for high-density deployment scenarios</li>
    <li>Optimized for high-concurrency startup scenarios</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Results</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Improved deployment density by <strong>1x</strong></li>
    <li>4 patents granted</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Kata Container</li>
    <li>QEMU</li>
    <li>DPU Virtualization</li>
    <li>VFIO</li>
  </ul>
</BlogLayout>
